full_text: Screened by NARA, 7/21/2023 U.S. Department of Justice Immigration and Naturalization Service WESTERN REGIONAL SERVICE CENTER P. 0. BOX 30111-30115 FOIA (b)(6) LAGUNA NIGUEL, CA 92607-0111 DATE: 8-15-94 FILE NUMBER: FOIA (b)(6) Your petition (Form I-751) is being returned to you along with the fee. Your case is still pending and awaiting return of this petition and fee with the supporting documents. The list of acceptable documents is listed in number 6 your I-751 Instruction page. Per Section 216.4 (a) (5) of INA, you must give INS certain documents with this application to show that your marriage was not entered into in order to evade the Immigration Laws of the United States. Failure to return this petition, fee and supporting documents in a timely manner will result in the termination of your conditional resident status. Sincerely, Joseph L. Thomas Center Director
